bib.title: Differential Elastic Cross Sections For Protonsbetween 10 And 22 Mev On Ca-40.

free_txt: Elastic Scattering at Forward Angles was Corrected on
A  500-Mu  Surface-Barrier  Detector  For  the  Delta-E
Detector and a Lithium-Drifted Silicon Detector For the
E-Detector.   The  Depth of the E-Detector was 2 mm at
Lower  Energies  and  3  mm  at  Higher  Energies.   In
Addition  to the E+Delta-E, There was a Second Detector
Used As a Monitor For the System.
Uncertainty of Corrections on Carbon and Oxygen
The Uncertainty in the Current Integration.
The Following Uncertainties were Included in
Calculating the Relative Errors For the Differential
Statistics on the Number of Counts in the Elastic Peak
And the Number of Counts Lost Because of the Dead Time
Of the Computer,the Uncertainty (25%) In the
Corrections For Carbon and Oxygen at Forward Angles,
The Uncertainty For Normalization of the Data,the
Two Targets were Used For Those Measurements. Both
Targets were Made from the Same Foil of Isotopically
Enriched Ca-40 Containing 99.97% of Ca-40. The Areal
Densities of these Targets were 2.67+-0.08 Mg/Cm**2
